CSE251 Sample OpenGL Code
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

About:
This is a simple program which draws a ball inside a box. This ball is given some velocity and collides with the boundaries.
There is also a triangle which can be moved around by the user.

How to run:
-> The makefile compiles the code. (Type 'make' on the terminal)
-> Now type './cse251_sampleCode' (on terminal) to run the executable. {linux}

Controls:
-> You can use the arrow keys to move around the triangle.
-> The left and right mouse buttons rotates the triangle.

Feel Free to contact any of the TA's for any help :)
Have Fun making games! :D

~Cheers~
Graphics TA's

